cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is about designing deep neural network architectures for multitask learning using evolutionary optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses improving performance in each task, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper specifically focuses on character recognition, which is a common topic in the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a common topic in the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of evolution to advance complex system design, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
